item.dc:creator: @bobby Bobby
item.description:
@bobby wrote:

and, that[quote=“R.I.P RSC, post:20, topic:67249”]Do you know, that if you use this for RS it could take a long time to get it right? Because some people use just random passwords like asdfpiedaf14. The max amount of characters in a RS password is 20. A password can contain 10 numbers (0,1,2,3…) and 26 letters. Thats a total of 36 characters available. 20^36=6,8719476736e+46 (I may be wrong) Now lets say 1 try takes 3 seconds. That would take 6,8719476736e+46*3=2,06158430208e+47 seconds. In minutes that is 3,4359738368e+45 and in hours its 5,7266230613333333333333333333333e+43.

After looking at this Im doubting its right because the numbers are way too big in my opinion. Anyways, brute forcing can be a long dreaded thing to do. :rolleyes:[/quote]

thats assuming that the passwird you try is the right one. it is unlikly, but it could be the first one you tty.
